                                    <td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
                                    <td>The <b>Emotion Wheel</b> (see left) was devised as a tool for the verbal report of
                                        emotions. It includes 16 emotion categories positioned in a circle. The 16
                                        categories are ordered according to their postulated position in a 2 dimensional
                                        space. The two underlying dimensions are the level of perceived <i>control</i> in the
                                        situation that generates the emotion (vertical dimension) and the positive/negative
                                        (pleasant/unpleasant) quality of the situation and of the resulting feeling
                                        also called <i>valence</i>(horizontal dimension).</td>
